    "Proteins are generally composed of one or more functional regions, commonly termed domains.",
    "Different combinations of domains give rise to the diverse range of proteins found in nature.",
    "The identification of domains that occur within proteins can therefore provide insights into their function.",
    "DeepBGC is a deep learning-based tool that uses a combination of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and recurrent neural networks (RNNs) to predict and classify BGCs in bacterial genomes.",
    "It processes raw genomic sequences to identify BGCs and provides detailed annotations of their functional components (Hannigan et al., 2019)."
